entries.meaning: Of or pertaining to the placenta. [from 18th c.]
(zoology) Pertaining to the Placentalia, comprising those mammals not marsupials or monotremes. [from 19th c.]
examples: We do not know exactly how many placental lineages  survived to leave descendants; most estimates are around ten.

entries.meaning: Any animal that is a member of the Placentalia
